9:
This kotatsu thing is wonderful... I'm
all cozy and toasty...
12: I'm gonna stay right here all day...
25:
Huh?!
Alk! Why'd you turn it off?
32: Could you wait outside for a minute?
37: No way! I'm not leaving this kotatsu!
40:
My mind's made up. I'm staying right
here all day—
51:
Argh... My holy sanctuary... Captured
by a raider!
54:
Well, well. Do my eyes deceive me,
or is that the Farlan saint herself?
57:
Oh, hello Razelt and Libram. Happy
New Year to you both.
61:
And the same to you, Orvelle.
However, this is neither the Farlands
nor the Church of Farlana.
64:
Is it all right for us to simply act as
old friends?
72:
You two! Gimme some New Year's
cash!
76:
Hahaha! Few folk are so bold as to
make demands of royalty! I haven't
much money on-hand, but how
much do you need?
81:
Nothing is worse than a destitute
prince. I have plenty of coin with me.
86:
Oh, how this one wounds me!
Lady Orvelle, allow me to provide
physical labor. Take this ticket for a
shoulder massage!
95:
Uh... You can have the tickets back,
thanks.
99:
I'll just take a little of the money.
Thank you very much for the New
Year's gift.
103: Woww! It's so soft and squishy!
108:
Good timing, you three. Would you
like to try mochi-pounding?
112:
Mochi? Is that the same stuff you
see at food stalls in Palpebra
sometimes?
115: Oh, wow! So this is how they make it!
125: If it's all right, I'd love to!
134:
Ain't no way those little arms are
gonna do the job. Here, let me help
you lift it.
139:
Thank you...
All right, here goes!
154:
Heh-heh! It feels weird and squishy...
In a good way!
159:
Sorry to rain on your parade, but
you're gonna have to hit it harder if
you want to prepare it right.
169:
Getting the rhythm right is the
secret.
182: Just take it slow for now.
206: I-I'm okay. It doesn't even hurt.
220: N-nope! I'm fine! Totally good now!
224:
Okay, then. Just keep resting for a
while.
228:
It isn't easy to relax in her presence,
is it? She's the very object of your
faith.
236:
...You've got it all wrong. My prayers
are entirely separate from any
dogma or conception of reality.
239:
Besides, Lady Stella isn't someone
you offer prayers to... More like a
good friend, or...
244:
Your words lack conviction. If you
really believed that, surely you
would seem more relaxed?
247:
I know you're normally a bold one.
When you got that fool prince
involved in things earlier before
breaking off the engagement... To
me, that was proof enough of who
you are by nature.
251: Of all the people to call me out...
262:
I brought the mochi. Would you... like
to try some?
271:
Lady Stella, I... I want to be your
friend, but I'm just so nervous...
275:
But I'll get used to it! It might take a
while, but...
279: Okay. I'm looking forward to it.
284:
S-so anyway, the first step in
building our friendship will be...
eating mochi together!
294:
Huh? They're gonna catch a cold
sleeping like that!
297: Well, maybe just for a little longer.
